FBIS3-57791 "drweu001_i_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 FRANCE Government Deports Iranian Suspects AU3012213693 Paris AFP in English 2105 GMT 30 Dec 93 AU3012213693 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Paris, Dec 30 (AFP) -- Two Iranians wanted by the Swiss authorities for the murder of an Iranian opposition leader have been expelled to Iran "for reasons of national interest", the prime minister's office said here late Thursday [30 December]. Mohsen Sharif Esfahani, 37, and Ahmad Taheri, 32, were expelled Wednesday, said the office of French Premier Edouard Balladur. The pair were suspected of involvement in the April 1990 murder near Geneva of Kazem Rajavi, brother of Mas'ud Rajavi, leader of the People's Mujahidin, an armed group opposed to the Iranian authorities.
